{"video_id": "uNxTVcIlg1A", "title": "Daily Evening Bhagavatam Discourse | SB 1.17.6-7 | HH Stoka Krishna Swami | 17-02-2023", "speaker": "HH Stoka Krishna Swami", "youtube_url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uNxTVcIlg1A", "duration": 954, "segments": [{"start": 0.0, "end": 30.0, "text": " ओम ज्ञानति मिरान्धस्या ज्ञानाञ्जनिषलाकया चक्षुरुन्मीलितं येनातस्मैश्री गुरवेनमहा नमाओमिष्णुपादाया कृष्णप्रिष्ठायभूतले श्रीमते भक्ति वेदान्त स्वामिन्नितिनामिने नमस्ते सारस्वते देवे गवरवाणी प्रच"}, {"start": 30.0, "end": 60.0, "text": " गदाधर श्रीवासाधी गवरभक्त वृण्दा हरे कृष्णा हरे कृष्णा कृष्ण कृष्णा हरे हरे हरे राम हरे रामा रामरामा हरे हरे ओम्नमो भगवते वासुदेवाया नारायणम नमस्कृत्या नरम्चैवनरोत्तमं देवीम सरस्वतीम व्यासं ततो जयम उदी"}, {"start": 60.0, "end": 87.64, "text": " This chapter is entitled Punishment and Reward of Kali. Kali represents the Kali Yuga, the present age. Time is passing on this earth planet and is measured in terms of the number of years, a particular age called Yuga Lass."}, {"start": 87.64, "end": 107.08, "text": " It's a very, very big time period. Like Kali Yuga, the present age, lasts 432,000 years or we can say 4,32,000 years."}, {"start": 107.54, "end": 116.42, "text": " Kali Yuga began about 5,000 years ago when Krishna appeared at the end of Dwapar Yuga."}, {"start": 116.42, "end": 133.72, "text": " Kali Yuga and Krishna went back to his personal abode after winding up his pastimes. The day Krishna left this earth planet and went back to his personal kingdom, that is when Kali Yuga began."}, {"start": 133.72, "end": 144.72, "text": " But the influence of the age of Kali, which is to bring in godlessness."}, {"start": 146.42000000000002, "end": 161.58, "text": " But the influence was actually not felt by the people because of the wonderful administration of Parikshit Maharaj and similar Krishna conscious kings."}, {"start": 162.64000000000001, "end": 168.18, "text": " So that is what will be described in this chapter, Punishment and Reward of Kali."}, {"start": 168.18, "end": 171.10000000000002, "text": " So the sixth verse."}, {"start": 176.42000000000002, "end": 189.42000000000002, "text": " The meaning of this verse is, you rogue."}, {"start": 189.42000000000002, "end": 201.88000000000002, "text": " It is Parikshit Maharaj addressing that Kali Purusha, the personality of Kali, who is beating a common bull in a secluded place."}, {"start": 202.58, "end": 205.94000000000003, "text": " Parikshit is addressing that Kali Purusha."}, {"start": 206.42000000000002, "end": 206.92000000000002, "text": " The meaning of this verse is, you rogue."}, {"start": 207.4, "end": 215.50000000000003, "text": " Do you dare beat an innocent cow because Lord Krishna and Arjuna, the carrier of Gandiva bow, are out of sight?"}, {"start": 215.98000000000002, "end": 225.82000000000002, "text": " Since you are beating the innocent in a secluded place, you are considered a culprit and therefore deserve to be killed."}, {"start": 229.34000000000003, "end": 236.4, "text": " So the king is pointing out the action of this king."}, {"start": 236.42000000000002, "end": 253.04000000000002, "text": " Kali Purusha is a criminal act and therefore he deserves to be killed death sentence or death"}, {"start": 253.04, "end": 271.64, "text": " penalty because an innocent cow is beaten in a secluded place so the cow should be given all kinds of"}, {"start": 271.64, "end": 281.84, "text": " protection against any harm including even just beating the cow"}, {"start": 283.04, "end": 289.42, "text": " so in the purport Srila Prabhupada says in a civilization where God is"}, {"start": 289.42, "end": 298.8, "text": " conspicuously banished and there is no devotee warrior like Arjuna the"}, {"start": 298.8, "end": 306.82000000000005, "text": " associates of the age of Kali take advantage of this lawless kingdom and"}, {"start": 306.82000000000005, "end": 312.74, "text": " arrange to kill innocent animals like the cow in secluded"}, {"start": 312.74, "end": 313.02000000000004, "text": " slaughterhouses."}, {"start": 313.04, "end": 321.74, "text": " Srila Prabhupada is comparing the present day status of the society is"}, {"start": 321.74, "end": 330.04, "text": " somewhat similar to the situation being described which Parikshita encountered"}, {"start": 330.04, "end": 337.88, "text": " the beginning of Kali Yuga so our present civilization is more or less a"}, {"start": 337.88, "end": 342.74, "text": " godless civilization as far as the rulers are concerned."}, {"start": 342.74, "end": 351.44, "text": " Those in power, political power or those in governmental authority they don't conduct the state in terms of the codes given by God the codes given in our authorized Vedic scriptures."}, {"start": 351.44, "end": 372.44, "text": " They don't conduct the state in terms of the codes given by God the codes given in our authorized Vedic scriptures."}, {"start": 372.74, "end": 383.74, "text": " In short they don't conduct the governance in accordance with the Dharma Shastras."}, {"start": 383.74, "end": 389.74, "text": " The Manu Smriti, Parashara Smriti or Yajna Valkya Smriti."}, {"start": 389.74, "end": 393.74, "text": " Perfect codes are given, perfect laws are given."}, {"start": 393.74, "end": 396.74, "text": " They are not man-made laws."}, {"start": 396.74, "end": 398.74, "text": " They are given by liberated souls."}, {"start": 398.74, "end": 400.74, "text": " They are not man-made laws."}, {"start": 400.74, "end": 401.74, "text": " They are given by liberated souls."}, {"start": 401.74, "end": 402.74, "text": " They are not man-made laws."}, {"start": 402.74, "end": 403.74, "text": " They are given by liberated souls."}, {"start": 403.74, "end": 406.74, "text": " So there is no mistake in them."}, {"start": 406.74, "end": 412.74, "text": " Neither there is any need to amend those laws from time to time."}, {"start": 412.74, "end": 414.74, "text": " There is no need of any amendment."}, {"start": 414.74, "end": 417.74, "text": " They are perfect laws."}, {"start": 417.74, "end": 425.74, "text": " So these present day rulers in this Kali Yuga especially"}, {"start": 425.74, "end": 431.74, "text": " God is conspicuously banished from their"}, {"start": 431.74, "end": 435.74, "text": " governance."}, {"start": 435.74, "end": 441.74, "text": " It's a godless state."}, {"start": 441.74, "end": 452.74, "text": " And the person's ruling are not exactly like Arjuna or Pariksit Maharaj"}, {"start": 452.74, "end": 457.74, "text": " in terms of conducting the state affairs"}, {"start": 457.74, "end": 460.74, "text": " in order to maintain law and order."}, {"start": 460.74, "end": 464.74, "text": " They don't conduct themselves properly."}, {"start": 464.74, "end": 467.74, "text": " Then, as Prabhupada says here,"}, {"start": 467.74, "end": 469.74, "text": " the associates of the age of Kali"}, {"start": 469.74, "end": 471.74, "text": " take advantage of this lawless kingdom"}, {"start": 471.74, "end": 475.74, "text": " and arrange to kill innocent animals like the cow"}, {"start": 475.74, "end": 477.74, "text": " in secluded slaughterhouses."}, {"start": 477.74, "end": 484.74, "text": " Nobody knows how the cow suffers in the slaughterhouse."}, {"start": 484.74, "end": 488.74, "text": " Formerly the killing was done in the butcher shop"}, {"start": 488.74, "end": 492.74, "text": " if at all animals were to be killed for meat."}, {"start": 492.74, "end": 503.74, "text": " But now, especially in the modernized states"}, {"start": 503.74, "end": 506.74, "text": " where modern technology is employed"}, {"start": 506.74, "end": 508.74, "text": " the people eat packed meat"}, {"start": 508.74, "end": 511.74, "text": " and they think it is like packed vegetables"}, {"start": 511.74, "end": 517.74, "text": " or packed biscuits or packed grains."}, {"start": 517.74, "end": 519.74, "text": " Like that they think."}, {"start": 519.74, "end": 521.74, "text": " No, it is not that."}, {"start": 521.74, "end": 526.74, "text": " It is very cruel killing of the animals"}, {"start": 526.74, "end": 529.74, "text": " who suffer so much."}, {"start": 529.74, "end": 532.74, "text": " Such murderers of animals."}, {"start": 532.74, "end": 535.74, "text": " See the word Prabhupada uses is murder."}, {"start": 535.74, "end": 540.74, "text": " That means somebody who is supposed to be protected"}, {"start": 540.74, "end": 545.74, "text": " is being killed unlawfully."}, {"start": 545.74, "end": 547.74, "text": " Is being killed unlawfully."}, {"start": 547.74, "end": 549.74, "text": " So such murderers of animals"}, {"start": 549.74, "end": 551.74, "text": " stand to be condemned to death"}, {"start": 551.74, "end": 553.74, "text": " by the order of a pious king"}, {"start": 553.74, "end": 555.74, "text": " like Maharaj Pariksit."}, {"start": 555.74, "end": 557.74, "text": " Pariksit Maharaj will not tolerate"}, {"start": 557.74, "end": 559.74, "text": " such a killing."}, {"start": 559.74, "end": 562.74, "text": " He doesn't even tolerate a beating of a cow."}, {"start": 562.74, "end": 565.74, "text": " What to speak of killing an animal like cow."}, {"start": 565.74, "end": 567.74, "text": " For a pious king"}, {"start": 567.74, "end": 569.74, "text": " the culprit who kills an animal"}, {"start": 569.74, "end": 571.74, "text": " in a secluded place"}, {"start": 571.74, "end": 573.74, "text": " is punishable by the death penalty"}, {"start": 573.74, "end": 575.74, "text": " exactly like a murderer"}, {"start": 575.74, "end": 578.74, "text": " who kills an innocent child"}, {"start": 578.74, "end": 580.74, "text": " in a secluded place."}, {"start": 580.74, "end": 582.74, "text": " Prabhupada gives a comparison."}, {"start": 582.74, "end": 584.74, "text": " If a child is killed"}, {"start": 584.74, "end": 586.74, "text": " it is helpless."}, {"start": 586.74, "end": 591.74, "text": " Supposing it is killed by some rogue."}, {"start": 591.74, "end": 594.74, "text": " That is the term used by Prabhupada"}, {"start": 594.74, "end": 597.74, "text": " for this Kali Purusha"}, {"start": 597.74, "end": 599.74, "text": " who is beating an innocent cow"}, {"start": 599.74, "end": 601.74, "text": " in a secluded place."}, {"start": 601.74, "end": 604.74, "text": " So it is exactly like killing a child."}, {"start": 605.74, "end": 607.74, "text": " Same way"}, {"start": 607.74, "end": 608.74, "text": " if a child is killed"}, {"start": 608.74, "end": 609.74, "text": " innocent child is killed"}, {"start": 609.74, "end": 611.74, "text": " in a secluded place."}, {"start": 611.74, "end": 613.74, "text": " Then the murderer"}, {"start": 613.74, "end": 618.74, "text": " is punishable by the death sentence."}, {"start": 618.74, "end": 620.74, "text": " Exactly like that."}, {"start": 620.74, "end": 623.74, "text": " Even the one who harms a cow"}, {"start": 623.74, "end": 625.74, "text": " should be actually"}, {"start": 625.74, "end": 628.74, "text": " punished by death penalty."}, {"start": 628.74, "end": 630.74, "text": " The seventh verse"}, {"start": 630.74, "end": 633.74, "text": " Tvamva brunala dhavalaha"}, {"start": 633.74, "end": 634.74, "text": " paadai niunah."}, {"start": 634.74, "end": 636.74, "text": " padacharan"}, {"start": 636.74, "end": 639.74, "text": " vrisharoopena kim kashchid"}, {"start": 639.74, "end": 642.74, "text": " devonah parikhedayan"}, {"start": 642.74, "end": 644.74, "text": " The meaning is"}, {"start": 644.74, "end": 646.74, "text": " Then he"}, {"start": 646.74, "end": 648.74, "text": " Maharaj Pariksit"}, {"start": 648.74, "end": 649.74, "text": " asked the bull"}, {"start": 649.74, "end": 652.74, "text": " O who are you?"}, {"start": 652.74, "end": 654.74, "text": " Are you a bull"}, {"start": 654.74, "end": 656.74, "text": " as white as a white lotus?"}, {"start": 656.74, "end": 658.74, "text": " Or are you a demigod?"}, {"start": 658.74, "end": 660.74, "text": " You have lost"}, {"start": 660.74, "end": 662.74, "text": " three of your legs"}, {"start": 662.74, "end": 663.74, "text": " and are moving on"}, {"start": 663.74, "end": 666.74, "text": " one only."}, {"start": 666.74, "end": 668.74, "text": " Are you some demigod"}, {"start": 668.74, "end": 669.74, "text": " causing us grief"}, {"start": 669.74, "end": 673.74, "text": " in the form of a bull?"}, {"start": 673.74, "end": 674.74, "text": " So Pariksit Maharaj"}, {"start": 674.74, "end": 680.74, "text": " is next questioning the bull."}, {"start": 680.74, "end": 681.74, "text": " Because"}, {"start": 681.74, "end": 683.74, "text": " the bull"}, {"start": 683.74, "end": 686.74, "text": " was not exactly like"}, {"start": 686.74, "end": 688.74, "text": " an ordinary bull."}, {"start": 688.74, "end": 692.74, "text": " As white as a white lotus."}, {"start": 692.74, "end": 694.74, "text": " So very very"}, {"start": 694.74, "end": 696.74, "text": " beautiful to look at."}, {"start": 696.74, "end": 698.74, "text": " Except that"}, {"start": 698.74, "end": 699.74, "text": " it had lost"}, {"start": 699.74, "end": 701.74, "text": " three legs"}, {"start": 701.74, "end": 702.74, "text": " and it was moving on"}, {"start": 702.74, "end": 704.74, "text": " only one leg."}, {"start": 704.74, "end": 705.74, "text": " So what was this"}, {"start": 705.74, "end": 707.74, "text": " bull trying to"}, {"start": 707.74, "end": 710.74, "text": " communicate?"}, {"start": 710.74, "end": 711.74, "text": " So he is wondering"}, {"start": 711.74, "end": 713.74, "text": " whether it is simply a bull"}, {"start": 713.74, "end": 714.74, "text": " or is it"}, {"start": 714.74, "end": 715.74, "text": " a devata"}, {"start": 715.74, "end": 717.74, "text": " who has come in the form of a bull"}, {"start": 717.74, "end": 720.74, "text": " to communicate something."}, {"start": 720.74, "end": 722.74, "text": " Are you some demigod"}, {"start": 722.74, "end": 723.74, "text": " causing us grief"}, {"start": 723.74, "end": 726.74, "text": " in the form of a bull?"}, {"start": 726.74, "end": 729.74, "text": " Indicating some"}, {"start": 729.74, "end": 731.74, "text": " misfortune"}, {"start": 731.74, "end": 733.74, "text": " some bad time"}, {"start": 733.74, "end": 734.74, "text": " is going to come"}, {"start": 734.74, "end": 736.74, "text": " or is"}, {"start": 736.74, "end": 738.74, "text": " foreboding some"}, {"start": 738.74, "end": 739.74, "text": " danger"}, {"start": 739.74, "end": 742.74, "text": " for such innocent animals."}, {"start": 742.74, "end": 743.74, "text": " So in the purport"}, {"start": 743.74, "end": 744.74, "text": " Srila Prabhupada says"}, {"start": 744.74, "end": 746.74, "text": " at least up to the time"}, {"start": 746.74, "end": 748.74, "text": " of Maharaj Pariksit"}, {"start": 748.74, "end": 749.74, "text": " no one could imagine"}, {"start": 749.74, "end": 751.74, "text": " the wretched conditions"}, {"start": 751.74, "end": 753.74, "text": " of the cow and the bull."}, {"start": 753.74, "end": 756.74, "text": " Maharaj Pariksit's time"}, {"start": 756.74, "end": 757.74, "text": " the cows and bulls"}, {"start": 757.74, "end": 760.74, "text": " were specially protected"}, {"start": 760.74, "end": 762.74, "text": " as much as the citizens"}, {"start": 762.74, "end": 763.74, "text": " human beings"}, {"start": 763.74, "end": 764.74, "text": " were protected"}, {"start": 764.74, "end": 766.74, "text": " completely"}, {"start": 766.74, "end": 768.74, "text": " by the powerful rulers"}, {"start": 768.74, "end": 771.74, "text": " like the Pandavas."}, {"start": 771.74, "end": 776.74, "text": " Pariksit Maharaj."}, {"start": 776.74, "end": 777.74, "text": " They were"}, {"start": 777.74, "end": 778.74, "text": " perfectly"}, {"start": 778.74, "end": 779.74, "text": " giving protection"}, {"start": 779.74, "end": 780.74, "text": " to those"}, {"start": 780.74, "end": 782.74, "text": " deserving protection"}, {"start": 782.74, "end": 783.74, "text": " the human beings"}, {"start": 783.74, "end": 784.74, "text": " and the cows"}, {"start": 784.74, "end": 787.74, "text": " and the bulls."}, {"start": 787.74, "end": 788.74, "text": " Maharaj Pariksit"}, {"start": 788.74, "end": 789.74, "text": " therefore"}, {"start": 789.74, "end": 790.74, "text": " was astonished"}, {"start": 790.74, "end": 793.74, "text": " to see such a horrible scene."}, {"start": 793.74, "end": 794.74, "text": " How dare somebody"}, {"start": 794.74, "end": 797.74, "text": " beat a cow"}, {"start": 797.74, "end": 798.74, "text": " and who has cut off"}, {"start": 798.74, "end": 800.74, "text": " the legs of the bull?"}, {"start": 800.74, "end": 801.74, "text": " Why is the bull"}, {"start": 801.74, "end": 805.74, "text": " standing on one leg?"}, {"start": 805.74, "end": 806.74, "text": " So"}, {"start": 806.74, "end": 807.74, "text": " Pariksit Maharaj"}, {"start": 807.74, "end": 809.74, "text": " inquired"}, {"start": 809.74, "end": 810.74, "text": " whether the bull"}, {"start": 810.74, "end": 811.74, "text": " was not a demigod"}, {"start": 811.74, "end": 815.74, "text": " assuming such a wretched condition"}, {"start": 815.74, "end": 817.74, "text": " to indicate the future"}, {"start": 817.74, "end": 820.74, "text": " of the cow and the bull."}, {"start": 820.74, "end": 822.74, "text": " Some message is being"}, {"start": 822.74, "end": 823.74, "text": " communicated"}, {"start": 823.74, "end": 825.74, "text": " that's what Pariksit thought."}, {"start": 825.74, "end": 828.74, "text": " It's a very very unusual scene"}, {"start": 828.74, "end": 830.74, "text": " in Pariksit's kingdom"}, {"start": 830.74, "end": 831.74, "text": " where"}, {"start": 831.74, "end": 833.74, "text": " perfect law and order was"}, {"start": 833.74, "end": 835.74, "text": " enforced by the powerful"}, {"start": 835.74, "end": 837.74, "text": " Emperor Pariksit"}, {"start": 837.74, "end": 839.74, "text": " based on"}, {"start": 839.74, "end": 840.74, "text": " the"}, {"start": 840.74, "end": 842.74, "text": " Dharma Shastras."}, {"start": 842.74, "end": 844.74, "text": " In the Bhagavad Gita"}, {"start": 844.74, "end": 845.74, "text": " Krishna says"}, {"start": 845.74, "end": 849.74, "text": " krishi go raksha vanijam"}, {"start": 849.74, "end": 852.74, "text": " vaisya karma svabhavajam"}, {"start": 852.74, "end": 854.74, "text": " A vaisya"}, {"start": 854.74, "end": 856.74, "text": " is supposed to"}, {"start": 856.74, "end": 858.74, "text": " protect cows"}, {"start": 858.74, "end": 861.74, "text": " engage in agricultural activity"}, {"start": 861.74, "end": 862.74, "text": " and"}, {"start": 862.74, "end": 864.74, "text": " trade and commerce"}, {"start": 864.74, "end": 866.74, "text": " for the upkeep of the society"}, {"start": 866.74, "end": 868.74, "text": " civilized society."}, {"start": 868.74, "end": 869.74, "text": " So"}, {"start": 869.74, "end": 872.74, "text": " he is inquiring"}, {"start": 872.74, "end": 874.74, "text": " Pariksit is inquiring"}, {"start": 874.74, "end": 875.74, "text": " from the bull"}, {"start": 875.74, "end": 877.74, "text": " are you a devata"}, {"start": 877.74, "end": 879.74, "text": " who is"}, {"start": 879.74, "end": 881.74, "text": " trying to give us some"}, {"start": 881.74, "end": 882.74, "text": " indication"}, {"start": 882.74, "end": 884.74, "text": " so that I may"}, {"start": 884.74, "end": 885.74, "text": " take some action"}, {"start": 885.74, "end": 886.74, "text": " I may correct something"}, {"start": 886.74, "end": 888.74, "text": " in my kingdom."}, {"start": 888.74, "end": 890.74, "text": " See the kings were so very"}, {"start": 890.74, "end": 892.74, "text": " sensitive"}, {"start": 892.74, "end": 894.74, "text": " and they would go around"}, {"start": 894.74, "end": 895.74, "text": " and see what is the condition"}, {"start": 895.74, "end": 897.74, "text": " of the"}, {"start": 897.74, "end": 898.74, "text": " people"}, {"start": 898.74, "end": 900.74, "text": " or the animals even"}, {"start": 900.74, "end": 901.74, "text": " which deserve protection"}, {"start": 901.74, "end": 902.74, "text": " what is happening"}, {"start": 902.74, "end": 903.74, "text": " in their kingdom"}, {"start": 903.74, "end": 905.74, "text": " they would go on a tour"}, {"start": 905.74, "end": 908.74, "text": " sometimes they would go incognito"}, {"start": 908.74, "end": 910.74, "text": " to"}, {"start": 910.74, "end": 911.74, "text": " find out"}, {"start": 911.74, "end": 913.74, "text": " the reality"}, {"start": 913.74, "end": 916.74, "text": " so like this"}, {"start": 916.74, "end": 919.74, "text": " the"}, {"start": 919.74, "end": 921.74, "text": " explanation is being given"}, {"start": 921.74, "end": 923.74, "text": " in the Bhagavad Gita"}, {"start": 923.74, "end": 924.74, "text": " the beginning of the"}, {"start": 924.74, "end": 927.74, "text": " age of Kali"}, {"start": 927.74, "end": 929.74, "text": " and the symptoms of Kali Yuga"}, {"start": 929.74, "end": 931.74, "text": " and 12th canto details are given"}, {"start": 931.74, "end": 933.74, "text": " of the symptoms of Kali Yuga"}, {"start": 933.74, "end": 935.74, "text": " and this solution is also given"}, {"start": 935.74, "end": 938.74, "text": " to overcome the"}, {"start": 938.74, "end": 941.74, "text": " defects of Kali Yuga"}, {"start": 941.74, "end": 943.74, "text": " what is to be done"}, {"start": 943.74, "end": 945.74, "text": " that is also explained"}, {"start": 945.74, "end": 947.74, "text": " in this chapter"}, {"start": 947.74, "end": 949.74, "text": " and in the Bhagavatam in general"}, {"start": 949.74, "end": 950.74, "text": " I will stop here"}, {"start": 950.74, "end": 951.74, "text": " thank you very much"}, {"start": 951.74, "end": 952.74, "text": " Hare Krishna"}]}